<h1>AgriPulse</h1>
<p><strong>Series:</strong> Pre-Seed &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Ask:</strong> ₹1.5 Crore (~$180,000 USD) &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Date:</strong> May 2026</p>

<hr />

<h2>The Problem</h2>
<p>India has 140 million smallholder farm households. 86% of them operate farms smaller than 5 acres and make irrigation decisions purely by guesswork — looking at soil colour, checking the weather on their phone, or asking a neighbour.</p>
<p>The result: Indian farmers over-irrigate by 35–40% on average (ICAR 2024 data), wasting scarce groundwater and losing crops to root rot, fungal infections, and nutrient runoff. Conservative estimates put annual crop losses from irrigation errors at ₹22,000 crore across Maharashtra alone.</p>
<p>Existing precision agriculture tools (Fasal, CropIn, Jivabhumi) cost ₹5,000–₹25,000 per acre annually — completely unaffordable for a farmer with 2 acres earning ₹3–4 lakh per year.</p>

<hr />

<h2>Our Solution</h2>
<p><strong>AgriPulse = ₹400 soil sensor + WhatsApp chatbot in Marathi</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Solar-powered LoRaWAN soil sensor: measures moisture, temperature, EC (electrical conductivity)</li>
<li>Battery life: 18 months on solar, no charging needed</li>
<li>Range: 2km LoRaWAN mesh — one gateway per 15–20 farms</li>
<li>Setup: 15 minutes, no technical knowledge required</li>
<li>Farmer receives daily WhatsApp message: <em>"Irrigate 45 minutes today. Skip tomorrow."</em></li>
<li>Available in Marathi, Hindi, and English</li>
<li>Works on basic 2G smartphones — no app download required</li>
</ul>

